  "text": "While the above works focus on unsupervised pre-training, [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] examine transfer learning via neural machine translation for NLU tasks like spoken language understanding and named entity recognition in the cross-lingual setting. They find that the results are mixed and for several NLU tasks, unsupervised pre-training actually outperforms its NMT counterpart. Our work shows that for NLG, machine translation substantially outperforms unsupervised pre-training objectives.",
